new_acknowledgment.subclause:
Spec at Item 4.0 commands `Get-Process -Name "Claude","Code" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Stop-Process -Force`. If EA-8 itself runs inside a Claude Desktop or VS Code Copilot session (likely default-LA behavior), this command terminates EA-8's own process mid-execution. Stage 4 single-continuous-block invariant breaks immediately.

AMENDMENT: prepend a self-termination preflight gate to Item 4.0:

```powershell
# EA-8 self-termination preflight (g8-ea8_n1(a))
# EA-8 MUST execute Stage 4 from a STANDALONE PowerShell console — NOT from inside a Claude Desktop or VS Code session.
# The Stop-Process command below will otherwise terminate EA-8's own session mid-cutover.
$ownPid = $PID
$ownName = (Get-Process -Id $ownPid).ProcessName
$parentName = ''
try {
  $parentPid = (Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter "ProcessId=$ownPid").ParentProcessId
  if ($parentPid) { $parentName = (Get-Process -Id $parentPid -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).ProcessName }
} catch {}
if ($ownName -match 'Claude|Code' -or $parentName -match 'Claude|Code') {
  throw "EA-8 is running inside an AI development surface (own=$ownName parent=$parentName). The Stop-Process step would kill EA-8. Relaunch in a standalone PowerShell console (Win+X → Windows PowerShell or Terminal) and re-attach the Stage 4 init pointer + Guide-#8 verdict before retrying Item 4.0."
}
Write-Host "Self-termination preflight: PASS (own=$ownName parent=$parentName)"
```

Then proceed with the original Item 4.0 commands as written.

Spec at Item 4.2 (lines 268-286): `cd C:\Users\mrbla\devplatform\tools\vikunja; Start-Process .\vikunja-v2.3.0-windows-4.0-amd64.exe` + 30-second polling for `/api/v1/info`. With g8-ea8_n1(c) Step (e) above already starting Vikunja and verifying reachability, Item 4.2 becomes redundant for the start step.
AMENDMENT: replace Item 4.2's command/verify with a POST-STARTUP verification triad that confirms (i) Vikunja resolved the DB at the absolute path; (ii) project count matches pre-cutover snapshot; (iii) DB sha256 stability across the first few seconds.
```powershell # (i) Confirm Vikunja read the absolutized DB (and not a fresh empty fallback) $expectedDb = "$env:LOCALAPPDATA\Vikunja\vikunja.db" $accidentalDb = "C:\Users\mrbla\devplatform\tools\vikunja\vikunja.db" if (Test-Path $accidentalDb) { $accLwt = (Get-Item $accidentalDb).LastWriteTime Write-Host "WARNING: $accidentalDb exists (LastWriteTime $accLwt). Verify this is the .pre_stage4_bak from rollback testing OR a Vikunja fresh-start fallback." } if (-not (Test-Path $expectedDb)) { throw "Expected DB at $expectedDb not found post-startup. ABORT." }
# (ii) REST cross-check: project count should match pre-cutover (>=10 per Stage 1 Vikunja Project IDs section) # If $env:VIKUNJA_TOKEN not set, fall back to user/pass auth per (see n1(e)) if (-not $env:VIKUNJA_TOKEN) { $cred = Get-Content C:\Users\mrbla\BlarAI\.vscode\mcp.json -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json $pass = $cred.servers.vikunja.env.VIKUNJA_PASS $body = @{ username='blarai'; password=$pass } | ConvertTo-Json $login = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri 'http://localhost:3456/api/v1/login' -Method POST -Body $body -ContentType 'application/json' $env:VIKUNJA_TOKEN = $login.token } $projects = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:3456/api/v1/projects" -Headers @{ Authorization = "Bearer $env:VIKUNJA_TOKEN" } Write-Host "REST project count: $($projects.Count) (expected >= 10 per Stage 1 ledger)" if ($projects.Count -lt 10) { throw "Project count below expected baseline ($($projects.Count) < 10). Vikunja may be reading a fresh empty DB. ABORT." }
# (iii) DB sha256 stability check (post-startup wait + re-hash) Start-Sleep -Seconds 3 $stableHash = (Get-FileHash $expectedDb -Algorithm SHA256).Hash Write-Host "DB sha256 at +5s post-startup: $stableHash" ```
Mark Items 4.1 and 4.2 as a logical pair: 4.1 establishes the absolutized config + start; 4.2 cross-validates the result. EA-8 may execute them as one continuous block.

Spec at Items 4.5 and 4.6 has the same scope as 4.4: repoint vikunja MCP entry to devplatform + F-1 fix. Same multi-field issue. Both files (BlarAI `.vscode/mcp.json` and BlarAI `.mcp.json`) need:
- command: rewrite to absolute devplatform .venv python path
- env.PYTHONPATH: add (BlarAI files don't currently set this)
- env.VIKUNJA_PASS: replace literal with `${env:VIKUNJA_PASS}`

AMENDMENT for Item 4.5 — final BlarAI `.vscode/mcp.json` `vikunja` block:

```jsonc
{
  "servers": {
    "vikunja": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "C:\\Users\\mrbla\\devplatform\\.venv\\Scripts\\python.exe",
      "args": ["-m", "tools.vikunja_mcp.server"],
      "env": {
        "VIKUNJA_URL": "http://localhost:3456",
        "VIKUNJA_USER": "blarai",
