```

Note: top-level key remains `servers` (NOT `mcpServers`). Per Stage 0 Anomaly A1 + Stage 3 g7-ea1_n13(c)(i)(ii) — schema must be preserved per file.

AMENDMENT for Item 4.6 — final BlarAI `.mcp.json` `vikunja` block: same content as 4.5 above EXCEPT top-level key is `mcpServers`. Other entries (`time`, etc.) unchanged.

Drop the spec phrase "BUT keep BlarAI's copy working as a fallback during the soak period" from Item 4.5 — per WORKFLOW_INTEGRITY A.4, all three MCP configs are repointed to devplatform; there is no "fallback BlarAI MCP" pattern post-cutover. devplatform's own .vscode/mcp.json (already correct from Stage 3.6) authoritatively serves the devplatform workspace; BlarAI's repointed configs serve the BlarAI workspace (which still uses devplatform's MCP server post-cutover).

Add same `` check as n1(f) for both files. Item 4.6's smoke_test step ("restart any one client") should be deferred to Item 4.11 per n1(l) — relaunching VS Code mid-Stage-4 is in tension with Item 4.0's closed-surfaces invariant.

Spec at Item 4.7.7 uses `Get-ScheduledTask | Where-Object { ($_ | Export-ScheduledTask) -match 'vikunja' }`. `Export-ScheduledTask` raises `The parameter is incorrect.` for ~40-50 protected/system tasks (current user can't export); the pipeline still completes but stderr is flooded with non-fatal exceptions. The match also yields false positives on the 6 BlarAI fleet tasks whose Description references `vikunja_mcp`.

AMENDMENT: suppress per-element Export-ScheduledTask exceptions + tighten regex to actual vikunja-autostart-shaped tasks only:

```powershell
$tasks = Get-ScheduledTask | Where-Object {
  try { ($_ | Export-ScheduledTask -ErrorAction Stop) -match 'vikunja-(autostart|web)' } catch { $false }
}
```

Behavior: enumerates only tasks that mention `vikunja-autostart` or `vikunja web` in their exported XML — i.e., tasks that actually launch Vikunja. The 6 fleet tasks whose Description contains `vikunja_mcp` are NOT autostart tasks and are correctly excluded.

Rest of Item 4.7.7 (BlarAI-substring throw + .lnk fallback warning) unchanged.
